?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
About socialism, it may sound great in practice it has never been implemented well.  There has always been severely decreased civil rights and millions of people killed.  The Soviet Union, China, Germany (the Nazi Party was a socialist movement, &quot;Nazi&quot; was slang for national socialism), Vietnam, North Korea, and Cuba are all perfect examples.<br>
<br>
While we're on the topic of taxes let me throw my belief in.  I believe there should be a flat tax rate where everyone pays a certain percentage of their income.  While I'm not quite sure what the exact percentage should be, I'm guessing it's around 20%. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=koji150>koji150</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.koji150.8m.com/koji.gif" BORDER=0> at: 9/30/03 1:53 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dynamiteneon>DynamiteNeon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>TBA</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/30/03 1:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12841.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mangaden.com/pics/junk/b.jpg width=75 length=75></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re Fun with Socialism</span><hr size=1> I actually agree with koji.  I can't see why it's unfair to take the same PERCENTAGE in taxes from every person.  Sure, the rich would pay more, but they would still have more than the others in the end.<br>
<br>
The government gets too much money to begin with, and they are mismanaging it.  They need to simplify the system, but realistically, those in power like it complicated since it's easier to take your money that way.<br>
<br>
Consider all the taxes you (more likely your parents) pay right now:<br>
sales tax<br>
federal taxes<br>
state taxes<br>
taxes on all your utilities<br>
property tax<br>
<br>
and there's more, but I can't think of them all right now.  It's absurd that we're paying somewhere between 40%-50% just in taxes.  Consider the fact that the Amercan revolution way back when was partially due to stupid taxes, and it shouldn't be too surprising that we're due for an overhaul.<br>
<br>
Of course, that sort of common sense idealism hardly ever gets you anywhere in a system like our's.  I think the last person to seriously suggest a flat tax was Forbes a few years back and he was just made out to be insane by the media for even suggesting it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aisuru@polykarbonbbs>aisuru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/30/03 5:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12841.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.aisuru.co.uk/saltire.jpg width=100 height=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re Fun with Socialism</span><hr size=1> i really dont understand why many of you can not understand the distinction between socialism and communism. <br>
<br>
communism is a much more extreme version of socialism, which shares many of it's principles, but does not intrinsically mean a dictatorship or oppression. the united kingdom has had many socialist governments throughout the 20th century, and still exists because SCOIALISM works. the soviet union no longer exists because COMMUNISM is flawed. you all seem to forget that tony blair is leader of the (left of centre) labour party, though his real personal political leanings are much in debate.<br>
<br>
anyway, socialism is not the same thing as communism. germany had a social democrat government for many years, through the seventies and early eighties and look at how strong their economy is. <br>
<br>
however the national socialist party, aka the nazis, of the thirties and early forties were not really socialist. one of the first groups of people that they persecuted was the communists. not exactly left-wing that, is it? national socialism meant socialism for the caucasian prodestant germans and nobody else. the nazis were extreme right wing, socialism is left wing. try applying a little logic koji <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
on the subject of taxes, why, if taxes were voluntary until the late forties, did a number of gangsters, including al capone, get sent to prison for tax evasion? <br>
