the boston tea party was <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>not</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a protest about the taxes on tea. the tax on tea that was levvied on the poeple of the british colonies in the 1770s was, in fact, LESS than the tax levvied on people in britain's tea. the party-goers were in fact smugglers, who objected to the fact that british tea, officially imported from the british colonies in india, actually undercut their own tea prices. taxes were not a problem unless you were a rich land owner, who could afford it. for example, the richest man in the americas, mr. george washington. <br>
